## 6. TESTING (Issue #104, #109)

### E2E Critical Paths

Required tests:
- Login flow
- Create Cliente → Edit → Delete
- Create Factura → Save → List
- CSV Import → Verify

### Component Testing

Every interactive component has tests:
- Renders correctly
- Handles user interactions
- Shows error states
- Accessibility checks

### a11y Testing

Use axe-core automated testing:
- No a11y violations in components
- Keyboard navigation works
- ARIA labels present

---

## 7. CODE QUALITY

### Before Every Commit

```bash
npm run lint              # ✅ Zero warnings
npm run type-check       # ✅ Zero errors
npm run test             # ✅ All tests pass
npm run test:e2e         # ✅ Critical paths pass
npm run check:i18n       # ✅ All 3 locales complete
```

### Commit Convention

```
feat(clientes): add bulk import dialog
fix(forms): validate CUIT on blur
docs(ui): add Button component story
test(critical-paths): add login flow
```

### Component Checklist

- [ ] Types for all props (TypeScript)
- [ ] No prop drilling > 2 levels
- [ ] Loading state handled
- [ ] Error state handled
- [ ] Mobile responsive
- [ ] Dark mode compatible
- [ ] Tests included
- [ ] i18n strings added
- [ ] Accessible (a11y)
- [ ] JSDoc comments

---

## 8. DOCUMENTATION (Issue #108)

### Storybook

Component stories showing all variants:
- Primary, secondary, disabled states
- Error/loading states
- Interactive examples
- Props documentation

---

## 9. PERFORMANCE (Issue #110)

### Code Splitting

Use React.lazy for large page components.

### Bundle Analysis

Track bundle size - no surprises.

### Web Vitals

Monitor LCP, FID, CLS.

---

## ANTI-PATTERNS

❌ useState in components > 5 times (extract hook)
❌ useEffect without dependency array
❌ Prop drilling > 2 levels
❌ console.error without user feedback
❌ Direct API calls in components
❌ No loading state
❌ No error handling
❌ Components > 200 lines
❌ Hardcoded values
❌ No tests for interactive components

